TVS Apache RR 310 Pure Racecraft - Ultimate Track Weapon\"/>\n|fuel_capacity    = {{Convert|11|l|abbr=on}}\n|related          =[[TVS Apache]]\n|sp               =  \n}}\nThe '''TVS Apache RR 310''' is a [[Types of motorcycles#Sport bike|sport bike]] made by the [[TVS Motor Company]] in collaboration with [[BMW Motorrad]] that was launched in India on December 6, 2017 .<ref name=\"TVS Apache RR 310 launched at Rs 2.05 lakh\">{{cite web|url=https://www.autocarindia.com/bike-news/2018-tvs-apache-rr-310-launched-at-rs-205-lakh-406757|title=2018 TVS Apache RR 310 Launched - TVS Apache RR 310 Price Rs 2.05 lakh - Autocar India|website=Autocar India|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref> It uses a {{cvt|312.2|cc|cuin}} [[Single-cylinder engine|single-cylinder]], [[Four-stroke engine|four-stroke]], [[spark-ignition|SI]], [[Radiator (engine cooling)|liquid-cooled]] reverse inclined engine.\n\nAlthough the Apache RR 310's engine is from BMW Motorrad's [[BMW G310R|BMW G310 R]] platform, the Apache is designed entirely by TVS's team in India. It is TVS's first [[Motorcycle fairing|fully-faired]] motorcycle.<ref name=\"TVS Apache RR 310 Price, Mileage, Review - TVS Bikes\">{{cite news |url=https://auto.ndtv.com/tvs-bikes/apache-rr-310|title=TVS Apache RR 310 Price, Mileage, Review - TVS Bikes|date=31 December 2017|website=NDTV Auto |accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Design ==\nThe Apache RR 310 is a fully faired motorcycle with sports-tourer style seating configuration. The engine uses a reverse inclined configuration. The bike has dual headlamps.\n\n== Updates ==\n\n===2020 Update===\nIn January 2020, the motorcycle was launched to cater to the newest emission norms of India known as [[Bharat stage emission standards|BS6]]. Power and torque output remained unchanged. A new colour named 'Titanium Black' was introduced, which replaced the recently introduced 'Phantom Black' colour. The motorcycle was also updated with features like colour [[TFT display|TFT]] screen instrument cluster with mobile phone connectivity and 4 riding modes (Urban, Rain, Sport, and Track). The other updates were newer ''[[Michelin]] Pilot Road 5'' tyres and the ''Glide Thru Technology Plus''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auto.ndtv.com/news/2020-bs6-tvs-apache-rr-310-launched-in-india-prices-start-at-rs-2-40-lakh-2172111|title=2020 BS6 TVS Apache RR 310 Launched In India; Prices Start At Rs. 2.40 Lakh|website=CarandBike|language=English|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n\n===2019 Update===\nIn May 2019, the motorcycle was updated with a slipper clutch, and the company also introduced a new colour named 'Phantom Black', which replaced the old 'Matte Black' colour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autocarindia.com/bike-news/2019-tvs-apache-rr-310-launched-at-rs-227-lakh-412869|title=2019 TVS Apache RR 310 launched at Rs 2.27 lakh|website=Autocar India|language=en|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref>\n==Performance==\nThe motorcycle's performance numbers as<ref name=\"TVS Apache RR 310 Pure Racecraft - Ultimate Track Weapon\">{{cite news |url=https://www.tvsapache.com/rr310/|title=TVS Apache RR 310 Pure Racecraft - Ultimate Track Weapon|date=5 December 2017|website=TVS Apache |accessdate=1 January 2018}}</ref> provided by the company are:-\n\n*Max. speed: {{Convert|160|km/h|abbr=on}}.\n*Acceleration (0-2sec): {{Convert|46.7|km/h|abbr=on}}.\n*0-{{Convert|60|km/h|abbr=on}}: (time in sec): 2.93 s.\n*0-{{Convert|100|km/h|abbr=on}}: (time in sec): 7.17s.\n\n== International launch ==\nIn September 2018, TVS launched the bike in Nepal, and in Peru in December 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.autocarindia.com/bike-news/tvs-apache-rr-310-rtr-160-4v-ntorq-125-launched-in-peru-410810|title=TVS Apache RR 310, RTR 160 4V, Ntorq 125 launched in Peru|website=Autocar India|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/auto/tvs-apache-rr-310-launched-in-nepal-company-forays-into-premium-bike-segment-1875489.html|title=TVS Apache RR 310 Launched 